    "summary": "Endophytic microorganisms hold immense promise as sources of diverse and potentially bioactive compounds, making them a focal point of investigation in natural product research. In this study, natural products have been explored from symbiotic fungi and bacteria isolated from organisms collected from three distinct collection sites in Egypt. The Orman Garden in Giza, the soda lakes of Wadi Natrun, and the coral reefs of Hurghada, representing ecologically diverse habitats rich in microbial diversity. The strains collected and cultured have most likely never been screened against disease targets and so have high potential to harbour novel bioactive natural products that have yet to be studied. A total of 31 samples were collected from these sites, yielding 87 microbial isolates: 12 isolates"
